M125A1 Signal Illuminant Green Star Cluster
 The M125A1 is primarily for signaling among ground troop emplacements and is occasionally used to signal aircraft. It consists of a five-star green cluster illuminant assembly and a rocket motor propulsion assembly all contained in a ten-inch hand-held aluminum launching tube. The fin stabilized rocket assembly propels the illuminant to an altitude of 300 feet after which an expelling charge ignites the illuminant and the assembly free falls to the ground and burns for 10 seconds at an intensity of 9,000 candlepower.Great for someone collecting. Vintage, 1970's. If post is up it is still available.

Barrel length was 24 inches, with sighting being done through a spring-leaf and elevator rear sight and bead front sight. Come with a period correct Sears green, lined zip case.
